	<body>
		<outline text="July 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="july2021" >
			<outline text="July 6" type="calendarDay" name="06" >
				<outline text="When my phone looks at the QR code on desktop @signalapp, it says &quot;No usable data found.&quot; Also, do these directions under the QR code mean Signal Settings in the phone's settings for Signal, or settings in the Signal app on the phone? I don't see either. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1412399194237767681/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 13:13:03 GMT" tweetId="1412399194237767681" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1412399194237767681" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 2" type="calendarDay" name="02" >
				<outline text="Follow this @google #streetview: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.google.com/maps/@50.2298044,-121.581646,3a,75y,9.21h,89.45t/data=!3m6!1e1!3m4!1seo6hwTGmRCRaiGkEPgnnAA!2e0!7i13312!8i6656?shorturl=1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; All of that is gone. Sympathies from California, where our home has come close to this twice so far. https://t.co/Zch552MSTv" type="tweet" created="Sat, 03 Jul 2021 01:57:01 GMT" tweetId="1411141901185650689" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1411141901185650689" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
				<outline text="Not a thread, but perhaps a thing: better #epitaphs
To get started: 
&quot;I was almost finished&quot; 
&quot;Sorry, I'm on mute&quot;
&quot;Finally, shovel-ready&quot;
&quot;Pardon my daisies&quot;
&quot;Can you step to the left, please? Thanks.&quot;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 17:17:13 GMT" tweetId="1411011086690750470" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1411011086690750470" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
				</outline>
			</outline>
		<outline text="June 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="june2021" >
			<outline text="June 30" type="calendarDay" name="30" >
				<outline text="What is the gesture on an @Apple magic mouse that  makes the tweet one is writing vanish without a trace, along with its tab? #Annoying doesn't cover how what that is." type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 14:05:43 GMT" tweetId="1410238119086018568" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1410238119086018568" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 28" type="calendarDay" name="28" >
				<outline text="My answer to an @Quora question about top 40 radio: https://t.co/b8k7a9DxFx" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 19:22:00 GMT" tweetId="1409592941518131205" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1409592941518131205" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
				<outline text="@RuffTimo says here https://t.co/c2dpV0t9MG that the EU's new #wallet https://t.co/Yc28HuZ4ow will be huge for #SSI. Anyone have first (eu) sources for that announcement and tech implementation plans?" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 14:53:17 GMT" tweetId="1409525315341275148" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1409525315341275148" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
				<outline text="I just re-logged in to Twitter through my @digime app. The flag @twitter sent me to review the login said I was in Staten Island rather than at the north end of Manhattan. This is no big deal, but does identify a feature of (rather than a bug in) how the Net's innards work." type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 13:38:13 GMT" tweetId="1409506422463860737" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1409506422463860737" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
				<outline text="I want a virtual (mirrored? replica'd?) phone on my computer, so I have an easier place to run all the useful apps that are only on phones." type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 13:32:05 GMT" tweetId="1409504879920529410" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1409504879920529410" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 26" type="calendarDay" name="26" >
				<outline text="A visit to the site of the historic Marconi wireless station on Cape Cod. https://t.co/eI2aAylRO1" type="tweet" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2021 19:57:16 GMT" tweetId="1408877039961190405" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1408877039961190405" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 24" type="calendarDay" name="24" >
				<outline text="Suddenly listening to @nprfreshair on the @Apple iOS app requires a $2.99/mo subscription. Apparently, no more listening on that app without it. Not required on @downcastapp, I see. Odd." type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 00:18:26 GMT" tweetId="1408217987711213570" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1408217987711213570" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
				<outline text="Nice @NetNewsWire review in @lifewiretech: https://t.co/QeSkjcwsAq Yo @brentsimmons" type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 23:06:07 GMT" tweetId="1408199787246239747" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1408199787246239747" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
				<outline text="The plan is to address my storage crisis https://t.co/0Nj1L7WJ5V with a cloud. Currently I'm leaning toward @backblaze, which @lifewiretech likes best: https://t.co/wZ16BTYghh . Advice welcome." type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 22:30:39 GMT" tweetId="1408190863063277570" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1408190863063277570" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
				<outline text="A storage crisis https://t.co/nhamLZt4le" type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 22:26:07 GMT" tweetId="1408189724980875277" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1408189724980875277" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
				<outline text="Redux 002: Listen Up https://t.co/33YC4APbog" type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 18:27:34 GMT" tweetId="1408129691882557451" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1408129691882557451" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
				<outline text="I just subscribed to Towers of Babel https://t.co/P6thZaqhvQ Reasons: I tend to agree (example on my side: https://t.co/1Z58tQg3iJ), which I'm not sure is a good thing, but there it is. Also, it's not too frequent. (I think I'm close to maxed on subs now.)" type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 16:24:07 GMT" tweetId="1408098622126841862" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1408098622126841862" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
