			<outline text="June 23" type="calendarDay" name="23" >
				<outline text="Fun show, even though I found at the end that I had been pronouncing @jriddell's surname wrong. Correct: &quot;Riddle.&quot; I also didn't notice that the typeface of @webmink's shirt is in comic sans. Otherwise all was perfect. https://t.co/6qz9yqOxjx" type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 01:43:15 GMT" tweetId="1407876945136828416" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1407876945136828416" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
				<outline text="@shoshanazuboff: &quot;I had a data scientist who said to me the other day, âLook, the underlying norm of all software and apps designed now is data collection.â For all intents and purposes, all of them are designed to engage in surveillance.&quot; In https://t.co/GltuGBokcn" type="tweet" created="Wed, 23 Jun 2021 15:36:40 GMT" tweetId="1407724295363731463" urltweet="https://twitter.com/dsearls/status/1407724295363731463" tweetUserName="dsearls" />
